games.comment: Eddie Royal.    Two plays before the touchdown, however, Cutler fumbled the football on an empty-handed throw, recovered by the Chargers. The play was ruled an incomplete pass, but after a challenge, Ed Hochuli turned it into a fumble, but allowed the Broncos to keep possession because he inadvertently blew his whistle when he thought Cutler tossed an incompletion. Hochuli made an error, but don't tell him that. He'll beat you down with his strong muscles if you do.    The other thing of note is that
Eddie Royal caught 7 balls for 111 yards and a touchdown, with 64 of those yards coming on 1 reception.
